\begin_layout Enumerate
(Optional) Tin the uncoated surface of the SHV jack body to ease making
 a good solder connection with the tube later.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Use a tip that will provide good heat transfer and set the soldering iron
 to it's highest temperature.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The entire SHV jack body will be heated to near the solder melting temperature,
 use something that doesn't conduct heat well to manipulate it, like a bunch
 of paper towels.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*
See figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:TinningSHVjack"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 for tinning the SHV jack.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Apply a small blob of solder to the uncoated surface of the SHV jack body.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Spread the blob of solder around the surface until it covers the entire
 surface where the nickel was removed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Remove any excess solder with fluxed solder wick.
