\begin_layout Enumerate
Solder the washer to the cable end of the tube.
 For the chosen washer and tube it should be a press fit.
 If it can't fit into the tube it can be soldered over the end, if it falls
 through it can be secured with Kapton tape to hold in place during initial
 soldering.
 The cable shield will be soldered here later so a large solder excess is
 fine.
 Make sure all gaps between the tube and washer are sealed as this is an
 oil boundry.
