\begin_layout Section
Assemble the resistors and capacitors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Assemble the capacitors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Place the capacitors and standoff in the jig.
 If using a 5 mm standoff place an M2.5 washer under the standoff for a spacer.
 Lightly tighten the bolts to hold the capacitors in place.
 The spring in the plastic jig will push the capacitors fully against the
 standoff when soldering without requiring significant deflection.
 Once tight, remove the washer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Test fit the capacitors to ensure they can be inserted in the tube, they
 will protrude slightly from one side of the jig.
 Some filing of the standoff or tube may be necessary.
 
\series bold
Do not file the resistors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Heat the standoff while applying additional solder to the capacitor to standoff
 joint until the solder flows.
 Then apply sufficient solder to fill the center of the standoff.
 Solder should flow along all the capacitors while spreading around the
 standoff.
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

