\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Attach the cable and tube
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Attach the cable
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assembly differs if the cable has a connector already that prevents adding
 the tube after the cable is already attached.
 If the cable doesn't have a connector on the end then not adding the tube
 until after the cable is attached makes it easier to handle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Cut a few millimeters of AWG 20 furrule and trim the resistor lead and cable
 center conductor to fit inside the furrule.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Tin the resistor lead and cable center conductor, leave a large solder blub
 so it will fill the furrle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The furrle has a copper body but is nickel plated, which is hard to remove
 from inside the tube and makes it hard to solder to.
 However, the solder joint between the resistor and wire should be good.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Slide the furrule over the resistor lead while heating the furrule until
 the solder melt and the furrle slides on fully.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
If the cable has a connector already, slide the cable through the grommet
 and tube first.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Heat the furrule and slide the cable all the way into the furrule.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Gently tug on the cable to ensure it made a good connection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Ensure there are no solder points that might cause discharges.
 No solder is required on the exterior of the tube, whcih should minimize
 the liklihood of pints.
 If the solder is hot enough before the heat is removed it will form a smooth
 surface before solidifying.
 If there is excessive solder on the tube exterior forming points, wick
 it away.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Clean the solder flux off the filter, this is the last chance to do so before
 the tube prevents easy access to the filter internals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Install the tube
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Remove any protective tape inside the filter and slide the tube into place.
 Ensure the capacitor pads are visable through the holes in the sides of
 the tube.
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

